Classification.Comment: The 8pterp23.1 copy number loss involves multiple genes. Patients with comparable or smaller deletions of this region have a variable phenotype, including developmental delay and/or intellectual disability, neurobehavioral disorders, and craniofacial abnormalities (Shi et al. Mol Med Rep. 2017 Nov;16(5):6837-6845. PMID: 28901431; Burnside et al. Am J Med Genet A. 2013 Apr;161A(4):822-8. PMID: 23495222; Chien et al. Clin Genet. 2010 Nov;78(5):449-56. PMID: 20236125).
